OL,3,CBritish reluctance to talk about death
OL,4,Ccosting bereaved #157m a year ` survey
OL,6,FThe British reluctance to talk about
OL,7,Fdeath could be costing bereaved loved
OL,8,Fones almost #157.1 million
OL,9,Fcollectively every year, a survey
OL,10,Fsuggests.
OL,12,FSome 59% of people who have arranged a
OL,13,Ffuneral spent beyond their means, with
OL,14,Fan average overspend of #513, a poll
OL,15,Ffor palliative care and bereavement
OL,16,Fcharity Sue Ryder found.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
