CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777246395
OL,3,CBritish reluctance to talk about death
OL,4,Ccosting bereaved #157m a year ` survey
OL,6,FAlmost a third (30%) of those who
OL,7,Foverspent felt pressure to do so, even
OL,8,Fif it stretched them beyond what they
OL,9,Fcould afford, while 26% worried about
OL,10,Fbeing judged if they chose a more
OL,11,Fmodest option.
OL,13,FAmong those who had experienced the
OL,14,Fdeath of a loved one in the past five
OL,15,Fyears, nearly a quarter (24%) had
OL,16,Fnever discussed end-of-life wishes.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
