CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777246395
OL,3,CBritish reluctance to talk about death
OL,4,Ccosting bereaved #157m a year ` survey
OL,6,FA further 23% revealed they were left
OL,7,Fconfused about what their loved one
OL,8,Fwould have wanted, and more than half
OL,9,F(56%) admitted this had resulted in
OL,10,Ffamily disagreements lasting an
OL,11,Faverage of 13 months.
OL,13,FAmong those who had disagreements
OL,14,Fwithin their family, more than two
OL,15,Fthirds (67%) said the rift was only
OL,16,Fresolved when another family member
OL,17,Fbecame ill.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
