OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777246395
OL,3,CBritish reluctance to talk about death
OL,4,Ccosting bereaved #157m a year ` survey
OL,6,FNearly half (48%) feel uneasy talking
OL,7,Fabout dying and death, while 47% said
OL,8,Fthey would not know how to start the
OL,9,Fconversation.
OL,11,FSue Ryder chief executive James
OL,12,FSanderson said: "The nation's silence
OL,13,Fabout the end of life, and death, can
OL,14,Fcarry a real cost, not just
OL,15,Femotionally, but financially too.
OL,26,@tD@QOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
