OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1777246395
OL,3,CBritish reluctance to talk about death
OL,4,Ccosting bereaved #157m a year ` survey
OL,6,FMore than half of those who had
OL,7,Fexperienced the death of a loved one
OL,8,Fwithin the past five years (53%) said
OL,9,Fthey did not know their loved one was
OL,10,Fnearing the end of life.
OL,12,FWhile 59% of those who have been
OL,13,Fbereaved regretted not having a proper
OL,14,Fopportunity to say goodbye, around
OL,15,Fhalf said unresolved issues and
OL,16,Funfinished conversations continued to
OL,17,Fweigh on them.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
